    "created_at": "2016-06-15T07:47:42Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-06-15T07:57:12Z",
    "body": "I found the culprit. It happens when you define one `filter` with only one extension in the `extensions` array.\n\nHere's a minimal example.\n[app.zip](https://github.com/electron/electron/files/315612/app.zip)\n\n**How to trigger the bug:**\n- npm install first\n- > npm start\n- click browse, select some file, the package.json in the same folder would be the quickest choice\n- press open, textbox gets filled\n- close electron now by pressing the X button on the top right corner\n- look at your cmd.exe / taskmanager, electron should still be running\n"
  },
